topics.body:
My only regret now is not having a part-time job at that railroad park that's literally a few minutes away from where I live. _And yes, it's an actual railroad park._

*The place for reference is called McCormick-Stillman Railroad Park.*
By the way, I was just there this weekend with my mom (for fun and lulz), and lots of people (mostly families and/or eager railfans) come here each and every day, and it's open almost year round.

This is one of the first things to greet you there:
!http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/50/SD-Magma_Arizona_Railroad_Engine_No._6-1906.jpg!

And this is one of the _actual jobs_ (not just volunteer, mind you) that I could have while working there.
!http://www.arizonaandpacificrr.com/projects/mccormick4.jpg!
Except it's hard to find any available jobs over there, and I think everything's booked for the summer.

_Even that one position that I'd love to have, where I get to drive a train around in circles all day long..._

*GOD. DAMMIT.*
